Widget based on jQuery UI, which combines UI autocomplete functionality with beautiful selected choices (tags)
Depends:

    * jQuery, jQuery UI autocomplete 

Using:

<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/path/to/folder/ui-auto-multiselect.css">
<script type="text/javascript" src="/path/to/folder/ui-auto-multiselect.js">
<script type="text/javascript">
    $(function() {
        $('#example').automultiselect({source:'/link/to/source/of/autocomplete'})
    })
</script>

Where $('#example') just a simple text input

<input type="text" id="example" />

Options:

source: url to autocomplete source or structure like [{'id':'1','value':'foo'},{'id':'2','value':'bar'}]

delay: delay before autocompletion

minLength: minimal amount of characters before autocompletion

prefix: prefix before name of hidden field

help: help text before or after text input

help_before: boolean, if true then help text will be rendered before text input, else after input

style: defines tag style: 'default' - use jQuery UI theme for rendering tags, also supported 'jira' style and 
       'stackoverflow' style